                     <div class="content" id="entry-300">
                        <h3 class="content">blueway</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img alt="blueway.jpg" src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/blueway.jpg" width="450" height="353" /></p>

<p><a href="http://itp.nyu.edu/show/detail.php?project_id=723">blueway</a>, another project at the itp spring show, is basically an interface for using the bluetooth devices people have as trackers, similar to the active badge stuff.  you register your device and have your picture taken at a kiosk, and then the devices are tracked and people's locations are displayed.  wayfinding information can also be presented to the users.  i don't exactly agree with this approach for a host of reasons.  one of the main ones being the registration hurdle, and the second being the picture/tracking business.  however, i just thought it was worth a mention.</p>
                              
                              <p class="posted">
                                 <span class="post-footers">roxy said on 08:05 PM</span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2006/05/blueway.html">Permalink</a>
                                 | <a href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2006/05/blueway.html#comments">Comments (0)</a>
                                 
                              </p>
                           </div>
