                     <a id="a000293"></a>
                     <div class="content" id="entry-293">
                        <h3 class="content">london tubemap mashups</h3>
                        <div class="content">
                           <div class="content">
                              <p><img alt="music-tubemap.jpg" src="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/music-tubemap.jpg" width="400" height="200" /></p>

<p>there's plenty of mashups of the iconic london tube map going around, and since i am going to be studying the underground this summer i'm definitely interested in these.  this one is a <a href="http://image.guardian.co.uk/sys-files/Guardian/documents/2006/02/02/underground5.pdf">music</a> version which tries to "plot the history of 20th century music."  the lines represent genres and their junctions and divergences are also used to reflect overlaps and offshoots within the music world.</p>

<p>i'd like to see one which represents the bands associated with each stop.  hmm... i guess that's why [karen, karma and i] embarking on our newest design project :]</p>

<p>[thanks <a href="http://www.boingboing.net/2006/02/04/musical_influences_m.html">boingboing</a>] </p>
                              
                              <p class="posted">
                                 <span class="post-footers">roxy said on 12:26 AM</span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2006/05/london_tubemap_mashups.html">Permalink</a>
                                 | <a href="http://drzaius.ics.uci.edu/blogs/setbang/2006/05/london_tubemap_mashups.html#comments">Comments (0)</a>
                                 
